S_BUCKET_NAME\\\", \\\"\\\").strip(),\\nprompts/05-backend-settings-and-secrets-loading.yolopilot.md:2205:    I traced the current health/status code paths too. The main design choice left is whether to keep a light custom loader or move to a stricter typed validator; I’m checking later storage prompts to choose names that won’t fight upcoming bucket work.\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nprompts/06-gitignore-and-secrets-hygiene.yolopilot.md:579:    ./prompts/05-backend-settings-and-secrets-loading.codex.jsonlines:97:{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_51\",\"type\":\"file_change\",\"changes\":[{\"path\":\"/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/secrets-and-local-config.md\",\"kind\":\"add\"},{\"path\":\"/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/secrets.example.yaml\",\"kind\":\"add\"}],\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\nprompts/06-gitignore-and-secrets-hygiene.yolopilot.md:584:    ./prompts/05-backend-settings-and-secrets-loading.codex.jsonlines:121:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_64\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc 'python -m pip install -r backend/requirements.txt'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"Requirement already satisfied: fastapi==0.116.1 in /opt/homebrew/Caskroom/miniconda/base/envs/storyteller/lib/python3.13/site-packages (from -r backend/requirements.txt (line 1)) (0.116.1)\\nRequirement already satisfied: httpx==0.28.1 in /opt/homebrew/Caskroom/miniconda/base/envs/storyteller/lib/python3.13/site-packages (from -r backend/requirements.txt (line 2)) (0.28.1)\\nCollecting PyYAML==6.0.2 (from -r backend/requirements.txt (line 3))\\n  Downloading PyYAML-6.0.2-cp313-cp313-macosx_11_0_arm64.whl.metadata (2.1 kB)\\nRequirement already satisfied: pytest==8.4.2 in /opt/homebrew/Caskroom/miniconda/base/envs/storyteller/lib/python3.13/site-packages (from -r backend/requirements.txt (line 4)) (8.4.2)\\nRequirement already satisfied: uvicorn==0.35.0 in /opt/homebrew/Caskroom/miniconda/base/envs/storyteller/lib/python3