{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_81","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented the prompt-17 realtime contract end to end. The core work is in [realtime.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/models/realtime.py), which adds typed subscription frames, a discriminated union for session events, explicit replayable vs ephemeral event shapes, session-channel naming, and schema export. I also added the human-readable contract doc at [realtime-events.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/realtime-events.md), the generated schema bundle at [realtime-events.schema.json](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/realtime-events.schema.json), contract coverage in [test_realtime_contracts.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/tests/test_realtime_contracts.py), and updated the model/doc index surfaces in [__init__.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/models/__init__.py) and [README.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/README.md).\n\nVerification was backend-focused because no UI code changed. I ran `./.venv/bin/ruff check app/models/realtime.py app/models/__init__.py tests/test_realtime_contracts.py`, `./.venv/bin/pytest tests/test_realtime_contracts.py tests/test_event_log_service.py`, and the full backend suite with `./.venv/bin/pytest`; all passed, with 44/44 backend tests green on the final full run. I did not run browser checks, screenshots, frontend tests, or a frontend build because this prompt only changed backend contracts, docs, and generated schema artifacts. I checkpointed the implementation in commit `784700f` (`feat(prompt-17): realtime event schema`).\n\nThe required reviewer summary file is written at [17-realtime-event-schema.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/17-realtime-event-schema.summary.md). Unrelated prompt-run artifact files that were already dirty were left untouched."}}
